Tested using: C4: 28gx3/38 g stainless steel fused Clapton at 45-60 watts&#xD;
&#xD;
This one is pretty light on the nose. What I am getting smells really good and kind of like a combination of spices, which would make sense for a bread pudding recipe.&#xD;
&#xD;
Wow. This is amazing right from the start. Everything that was promised is in here. Apple, booze, and a bread soaked in custard. I can't even begin to guess what might be in here other than maybe PUR Country Apple because the apple tastes cooked. &#xD;
&#xD;
I had to look at the recipe right away on this one because I really wanted to know how you got the bread pudding aspect in this. This recipe is almost hard to write a review for because there is not anything that I am wishing was here and there is nothing that I would take out. The combination of FE French Toast and FA Zeppola make a very convincing "bread," INW Custard was the perfect custard choice, and the spices from FLV Eggnog and FW Hazelnut make me really want to try your real life recipe. My only complaint is now I have to buy FLV eggnog and FE French Toast. Amazing recipe Fo!
